            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ESomething%20about%20the%20comfort%20and%20safety%20of%20the%20boat%20makes%20it%20hard%20to%20leave!%20After%20Noah%20had%20floated%20in%20the%20ark%20for%20months%2C%20God%20caused%20the%20floodwaters%20to%20recede%20and%20directed%20Noah%20and%20his%20family%20to%20leave%20their%20haven%20of%20refuge.%20Surely%20Noah%20wondered%20what%20it%20would%20be%20like%20outside%20the%20ark.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPeter%2C%20too%2C%20knew%20the%20safety%20of%20the%20boat.%20But%20one%20day%20Jesus%20challenged%20him%20to%20leave%20the%20known%20and%20enter%20the%20unknown%20realm%20of%20%22fishing%20for%20men.%22%20Can't%20you%20just%20imagine%20how%20Peter%20must%20have%20felt%3F%20What%20would%20it%20be%20like%20to%20wake%20up%20every%20day%20and%20follow%20Jesus%3F%20he%20must%20have%20thought.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20boat%20represents%20old%20habits%2C%20securities%2C%20and%20ways%20of%20doing%20things.%20Peter%20had%20been%20a%20fisherman%20for%20years%3B%20Noah%20had%20been%20confined%20to%20the%20security%20of%20the%20ark%20for%20months.%20Both%20had%20to%20decide%20if%20they%20would%20dare%20to%20follow%20the%20One%20who%20called%20them.%20When%20Noah%20sent%20the%20dove%20out%20the%20second%20time%20and%20it%20did%20not%20return%20to%20him%20(Genesis%208%3A12)%2C%20he%20knew%20it%20was%20time%20to%20leave%20the%20ark.%20Like%20the%20dove%2C%20he%20had%20no%20desire%20to%20stay%20in%20his%20world%20of%20former%20security.%20When%20Peter%20heard%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20Master%2C%20he%20knew%20it%20was%20time%20to%20leave%20the%20place%20of%20family%20refuge%20and%20follow%20the%20will%20of%20God.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOnce%20you%20have%20tasted%20of%20a%20new%20world-a%20world%20of%20ministry-you%20will%20have%20no%20desire%20to%20return%20to%20the%20mundane%20routine%20of%20life.%20Leave%20the%20boat%2C%20my%20Christian%20friend.%20A%20new%20world%20awaits%20you!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
