            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Genesis.8:1-10:32",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EGenesis%208%3A1-10%3A32%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_1%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EGenesis%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Flood%20Recedes%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20God%20remembered%20Noah%20and%20all%20the%20wild%20animals%20and%20livestock%20with%20him%20in%20the%20boat.%20He%20sent%20a%20wind%20to%20blow%20across%20the%20earth%2C%20and%20the%20floodwaters%20began%20to%20recede.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_2%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20underground%20waters%20stopped%20flowing%2C%20and%20the%20torrential%20rains%20from%20the%20sky%20were%20stopped.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_3%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20floodwaters%20gradually%20receded%20from%20the%20earth.%20After%20150%26%23xA0%3Bdays%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_4%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3Eexactly%20five%20months%20from%20the%20time%20the%20flood%20began%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E8%3A4%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eon%20the%20seventeenth%20day%20of%20the%20seventh%20month%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20see%207%3A11.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20boat%20came%20to%20rest%20on%20the%20mountains%20of%20Ararat.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_5%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3ETwo%20and%20a%20half%20months%20later%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E8%3A5%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EOn%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20tenth%20month%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20see%207%3A11%20and%20note%20on%208%3A4.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20as%20the%20waters%20continued%20to%20go%20down%2C%20other%20mountain%20peaks%20became%20visible.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_6%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20another%20forty%20days%2C%20Noah%20opened%20the%20window%20he%20had%20made%20in%20the%20boat%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_7%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20released%20a%20raven.%20The%20bird%20flew%20back%20and%20forth%20until%20the%20floodwaters%20on%20the%20earth%20had%20dried%20up.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_8%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20also%20released%20a%20dove%20to%20see%20if%20the%20water%20had%20receded%20and%20it%20could%20find%20dry%20ground.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_9%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20dove%20could%20find%20no%20place%20to%20land%20because%20the%20water%20still%20covered%20the%20ground.%20So%20it%20returned%20to%20the%20boat%2C%20and%20Noah%20held%20out%20his%20hand%20and%20drew%20the%20dove%20back%20inside.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_10%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20waiting%20another%20seven%20days%2C%20Noah%20released%20the%20dove%20again.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_11%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20time%20the%20dove%20returned%20to%20him%20in%20the%20evening%20with%20a%20fresh%20olive%20leaf%20in%20its%20beak.%20Then%20Noah%20knew%20that%20the%20floodwaters%20were%20almost%20gone.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_12%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20waited%20another%20seven%20days%20and%20then%20released%20the%20dove%20again.%20This%20time%20it%20did%20not%20come%20back.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_13%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3ENoah%20was%20now%20601%26%23xA0%3Byears%20old.%20On%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20new%20year%2C%20ten%20and%20a%20half%20months%20after%20the%20flood%20began%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E8%3A13%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EOn%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20first%20month%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20see%207%3A11.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20floodwaters%20had%20almost%20dried%20up%20from%20the%20earth.%20Noah%20lifted%20back%20the%20covering%20of%20the%20boat%20and%20saw%20that%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20ground%20was%20drying.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_14%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3ETwo%20more%20months%20went%20by%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E8%3A14%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EThe%20twenty-seventh%20day%20of%20the%20second%20month%20arrived%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20see%20note%20on%208%3A13.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20at%20last%20the%20earth%20was%20dry!%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_15%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20God%20said%20to%20Noah%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_16%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BLeave%20the%20boat%2C%20all%20of%20you%26%23x2014%3Byou%20and%20your%20wife%2C%20and%20your%20sons%20and%20their%20wives.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_17%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3ERelease%20all%20the%20animals%26%23x2014%3Bthe%20birds%2C%20the%20livestock%2C%20and%20the%20small%20animals%20that%20scurry%20along%20the%20ground%26%23x2014%3Bso%20they%20can%20be%20fruitful%20and%20multiply%20throughout%20the%20earth.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_18%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Noah%2C%20his%20wife%2C%20and%20his%20sons%20and%20their%20wives%20left%20the%20boat.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_19%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20all%20of%20the%20large%20and%20small%20animals%20and%20birds%20came%20out%20of%20the%20boat%2C%20pair%20by%20pair.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_20%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Noah%20built%20an%20altar%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20and%20there%20he%20sacrificed%20as%20burnt%20offerings%20the%20animals%20and%20birds%20that%20had%20been%20approved%20for%20that%20purpose.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E8%3A20%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eevery%20clean%20animal%20and%20every%20clean%20bird.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_21%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20pleased%20with%20the%20aroma%20of%20the%20sacrifice%20and%20said%20to%20himself%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20will%20never%20again%20curse%20the%20ground%20because%20of%20the%20human%20race%2C%20even%20though%20everything%20they%20think%20or%20imagine%20is%20bent%20toward%20evil%20from%20childhood.%20I%20will%20never%20again%20destroy%20all%20living%20things.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_8_22%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20long%20as%20the%20earth%20remains%2C%20there%20will%20be%20planting%20and%20harvest%2C%20cold%20and%20heat%2C%20summer%20and%20winter%2C%20day%20and%20night.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_9_1%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EGenesis%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EGod%20Confirms%20His%20Covenant%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20God%20blessed%20Noah%20and%20his%20sons%20and%20told%20them%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BBe%20fruitful%20and%20multiply.%20Fill%20the%20earth.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_9_2%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EAll%20the%20animals%20of%20the%20earth%2C%20all%20the%20birds%20of%20the%20sky%2C%20all%20the%20small%20animals%20that%20scurry%20along%20the%20ground%2C%20and%20all%20the%20fish%20in%20the%20sea%20will%20look%20on%20you%20with%20fear%20and%20terror.%20I%20have%20placed%20them%20in%20your%20power.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_9_3%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20have%20given%20them%20to%20you%20for%20food%2C%20just%20as%20I%20have%20given%20you%20grain%20and%20vegetables.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_9_4%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20you%20must%20never%20eat%20any%20meat%20that%20still%20has%20the%20lifeblood%20in%20it.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_9_5%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BAnd%20I%20will%20require%20the%20blood%20of%20anyone%20who%20takes%20another%20person%26%23x2019%3Bs%20life.%20If%20a%20wild%20animal%20kills%20a%20person%2C%20it%20must%20die.%20And%20anyone%20who%20murders%20a%20fellow%20human%20must%20die.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_9_6%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EIf%20anyone%20takes%20a%20human%20life%2C%20that%20person%26%23x2019%3Bs%20life%20will%20also%20be%20taken%20by%20human%20hands.%20For%20God%20made%20human%20beings%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E9%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Eman%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3Eha-adam.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20in%20his%20own%20image.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_9_7%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20be%20fruitful%20and%20multiply%2C%20and%20repopulate%20the%20earth.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_9_8%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%229%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2